### Connections with Low-rank Adaptation

Different from OFT and BOFT, HRA can also be viewed as an adaptive low-rank adapter. Specifically, we can rewrite the chain of HRs in equation 1 in the following equivalent format:

\[\bm{H}^{(r)}=\overleftarrow{\prod}_{i=1}^{r}(\bm{I}-2\bm{u}_{i}\bm{u}_{i}^{ \top})=\bm{I}+\bm{U}_{r}\bm{\Gamma}_{r}\bm{U}_{r}^{\top},\] (3)

where \(\bm{U}_{r}=[\bm{u}_{1},...,\bm{u}_{r}]\in\mathbb{R}^{d\times r}\), \(\bm{\Gamma}_{r}=[\gamma_{ij}]\in\mathbb{R}^{r\times r}\) is an upper-triangular matrix, and it can be defined as

\[\bm{\Gamma}_{1}=-2,\ \bm{\Gamma}_{r}=\begin{bmatrix}\bm{\Gamma}_{r-1}&-2\bm{ \Gamma}_{r-1}\bm{U}_{r-1}^{\top}\bm{u}_{r}\\ \bm{0}_{r-1}^{\top}&-2\end{bmatrix}.\] (4)

Accordingly, we have

\[\bm{WH}^{(r)}=\bm{W}+\bm{WU}_{r}\bm{\Gamma}_{r}\bm{U}_{r}^{\top}=\bm{W}+\bm{A} (\bm{W},\bm{B})\bm{B}.\] (5)

The above formulation can be viewed as an adaptive LoRA that inherits the theoretical guarantee of OFT on the retention of pre-training knowledge. The low-rank matrix \(\bm{B}=\bm{U}_{r}\), is constructed by normalized vectors, while the low-rank matrix \(\bm{A}=[\bm{a}_{1},...,\bm{a}_{r}]\) is parameterized as \(\bm{WU}_{r}\bm{\Gamma}_{r}\), which can be treated as a function of \(\bm{W}\) and \(\bm{B}\). Therefore, similar to OFT and BOFT, HRA ensures that the columns of \(\bm{WH}^{(r)}\) are always in the column space of \(\bm{W}\).

